# Sales Dashboard – Power BI Practice Project

## Overview
This project is a Sales Dashboard created in Power BI using the SuperStore Sales Dataset.  
The dashboard helps analyze sales performance, profit trends, customer segments, and regional insights through interactive visualizations.
Power BI practice project based on a Risham Mishra YouTube tutorial.

## Objective
The goal of this dashboard is to provide insights into:
- Sales and profit performance
- Regional sales trends
- Customer and segment analysis
- Category-wise performance
- Interactive business reporting

## Tools & Technologies Used
- Power BI
- Excel / CSV Dataset
- Data Visualization
- Business Analytics Concepts

## Dataset Used
The project uses the **SuperStore Sales Dataset** containing:

- Sales Data
- Profit Data
- Customer Details
- Regional Information
- Product Categories
- Shipping Details

## Dashboard Features
- Sales Overview
- Profit Analysis
- Regional Insights
- Customer Segment Analysis
- Interactive Filters & Slicers
- KPI Cards and Trend Charts

## Learning Outcomes
Through this project, I learned:
- Data cleaning and transformation
- Creating interactive dashboards in Power BI
- Using charts, slicers, and KPI cards
- Building business insights visually
- Dashboard design and reporting basics

## Project Files
- `DASHBOARD.pbix` → Power BI dashboard file
- `SuperStore Sales DataSet.xlsx` → Excel dataset
- `SuperStore_Sales_Dataset.csv` → CSV dataset

## Reference
Practice project inspired by the YouTube tutorial by **Risham Mishra** on creating a Sales Dashboard in Power BI.
